          "name": "Swarm",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 218,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "GM Core pg. 334",
                "aonid": 218,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "GM Core pg. 334",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "GM Core",
              "page": 334,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A swarm is a mass or cloud of creatures that functions as one monster. Its size entry gives the size of the entire mass, though for most swarms, the individual creatures that make up that mass are Tiny. A swarm can occupy the same space as other creatures and must do so in order to use its damaging action. A swarm typically has weakness to effects that deal damage over an area (like area spells and splash weapons). Swarms are immune to the grappled, prone, and restrained conditions.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "7c548a9e0a2647c082989720b3de0a87",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Wood",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 463,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the wood trait conjure or manipulate wood. Those that manipulate wood have no effect in an area without wood. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of wood or have a connection to magical wood.  \n  \nThese planes consist of trees and other flora latticed in organic patterns. Wood planes are often perfectly constructed to match their desired purpose or environment but aren\u2019t usually outright hostile to visitors.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
